quran[58]{c,v,t}:
  75,1,I swear by the Day of Resurrection
  75,2,and I swear by the self-reproaching soul
  75,3,Does man think that We cannot reassemble his bones
  75,4,"In fact, We are able to restore even his very fingertips"
  75,5,But man desires to persists in his evil ways
  75,6,"and asks [mockingly], “When is the Day of Resurrection?”"
  75,7,But when eyes are dazzled
  75,8,and the moon is darkened
  75,9,and the sun and the moon are brought together
  75,10,"on that Day man will say, “Where is the escape?”"
  75,11,No indeed! There will be no refuge
  75,12,On that Day all will end up before your Lord
  75,13,On that Day man will be informed of what he has sent forth and left behind
  75,14,"In fact, man will be a witness against himself"
  75,15,despite the excuses he may put forward
  75,16,"Do not move your tongue [O Prophet] in haste trying to memorize it"
  75,17,It is upon Us to make you memorize and recite it
  75,18,"Then when We recite it [through Gabriel], follow its recitation attentively"
  75,19,then it is upon Us to explain its meanings
  75,20,"No indeed! You [people] love this fleeting world"
  75,21,and neglect the Hereafter
  75,22,On that Day some faces will be bright
  75,23,looking at their Lord
  75,24,"And on that Day, some faces will be gloomy"
  75,25,knowing that a crushing calamity will befall them
  75,26,"Indeed, when the soul reaches the throat"
  75,27,"and it is said, “Is there any healer?”"
  75,28,And he realizes that it is time to depart
  75,29,"when legs are brought together [in a shroud]"
  75,30,"on that Day, he will be driven to your Lord"
  75,31,He neither believed nor prayed
  75,32,rather he denied and turned away
  75,33,then went swaggering to his people
  75,34,"Woe to you [O man], and woe"
  75,35,"Again, woe to you, and woe"
  75,36,Does man think that he will be left neglected
  75,37,Was he not once a drop of semen emitted
  75,38,"then he became a clinging clot, then He created him and perfected his form"
  75,39,"and made from him both genders, male and female"
  75,40,Is not He able to bring the dead back to life
  76,1,"Was there not a period of time when man was not a thing [even] mentioned"
  76,2,"Indeed, We created man from a drop of mixed fluids, in order to test him. So We gave him hearing and sight"
  76,3,"Indeed, We showed him the way, whether he is grateful or ungrateful"
  76,4,"We have surely prepared for the disbelievers chains, shackles, and a Blazing Fire"
  76,5,"Indeed, the righteous will drink from a cup [of wine] flavored with camphor"
  76,6,"a spring from which Allah’s slaves will drink, which will flow as they wish"
  76,7,They fulfill their vows and fear a Day whose evil will spread far and wide
  76,8,"and they give food, despite their love for it, to the needy, the orphans, and the captives"
  76,9,"[saying to themselves] “We feed you only for the sake of Allah; we seek from you neither reward nor gratitude"
  76,10,We fear from our Lord a grim and distressful Day.”
  76,11,"So Allah will protect them from the evil of that Day, and will grant them radiance and delight"
  76,12,and will reward them for their perseverance with Paradise and garments of silk
  76,13,They will recline therein on adorned couches; neither feeling scorching heat nor freezing cold
  76,14,"with shady branches spread above them, and clusters of fruit will be made within their reach"
  76,15,They will be served frequently with silver vessels and crystal cups
  76,16,"crystalline goblets of silver, filled precisely as desired"
  76,17,"They will be given a glass [of wine] flavored with ginger"
  76,18,from a spring therein called Salsabīl